'''康诺特广场'''（Connaught Square）是英国伦敦[[西敏市|西敏市]][[贝斯沃特|贝斯沃特]]区的第一个住宅广场，位于[[海德公园|海德公园]]以北，毗邻[[大理石拱门|大理石拱门]]和[[牛津街|牛津街]]西端。

它得名于曾住在附近的格洛斯特公爵（也是康诺特伯爵）。广场目前的外观形成于1820年代。

康诺特广场的建筑主要是乔治式建筑。

==布莱尔官邸==
2004年10月，当时的[[总理|总理]][[布莱尔|布莱尔]]和他的妻子切丽以350万英镑购买康诺特广场西侧的房子。<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk_politics/3707520.stm The house that Tony bought] {{Wayback|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk_politics/3707520.stm |date=20170802151501 }}, [[BBC_News|BBC News]], 1 October 2004.</ref>在许多方面，布莱尔官邸类似于[[唐宁街10号|唐宁街10号]]。现在布置有相当的警力，至少有四名[[伦敦警察厅|伦敦警察厅]]的警官。<ref>[http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1218408/Your-2m-year-guard-Tony-Blair-Former-PM-15m-leaving-office.html Your £2m a year bill to guard Tony Blair] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1218408/Your-2m-year-guard-Tony-Blair-Former-PM-15m-leaving-office.html |date=20220115233415 }} ''[[Daily_Mail|Daily Mail]]''. Published 6 October 2009. Retrieved 6 October 2009.</ref><ref name="indy">[http://www.independent.co.uk/opinion/columnists/claudia-winkleman/claudia-winkleman-take-it-from-me-449062.html Claudia Winkleman: Take It From Me - Blair's moving in] {{Wayback|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/opinion/columnists/claudia-winkleman/claudia-winkleman-take-it-from-me-449062.html |date=20091124075933 }} ''[[The_Independent|The Independent]]'' (London). Published 16 May 2007. Retrieved 30 May 2009.</ref> 布莱尔在2007年辞职后，该广场的保安安排存在争议，特别是提供24小时高级别安全的费用。<ref>[http://www.dailymail.co.uk/pages/live/articles/news/news.html?in_article_id=463984&in_page_id=1770 The great Connaught Square Revolt: Residents anger over Blair's new home] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/pages/live/articles/news/news.html?in_article_id=463984&in_page_id=1770 |date=20070929104842 }}, ''[[Daily_Mail|Daily Mail]]'' (London), 23 June 2007.</ref><ref name="dm">[http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1218408/Your-2m-year-guard-Tony-Blair-Former-PM-15m-leaving-office.html Your £2m a year bill to guard Tony Blair] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1218408/Your-2m-year-guard-Tony-Blair-Former-PM-15m-leaving-office.html |date=20220115233415 }} ''[[Daily_Mail|Daily Mail]]'' (London). Published 6 October 2009. Retrieved 6 O